opo&s;es lord Dudley as an husband for the Scotti&s;h queen. &sect; <HI>XXIV.</HI> The mu|tual animo&s;ity and di&s;&s;imulation of both queens. &sect; <HI>XXV.</HI> Lord Darnley arrives in Scotland. &sect; <HI>XXVI.</HI> And is married to the queen of that country, contrary to the advice of Elizabeth. The earl of Murray, and the revolting Scotti&s;h lords take refuge in England. &sect; <HI>XXVII.</HI> Mary engages in the catholic league of Bayonne. &sect; <HI>XXVIII.</HI> David Riccio is a&s;&s;a&s;&s;inated in the pre&s;ence of queen Mary.
