 who is removed to Hur&s;t Ca&s;tle. &sect; <HI>LII.</HI> The com|mons purged by the army. &sect; <HI>LIII.</HI> The independent intere&s;t prevails in parlia|ment. &sect; <HI>LIV.</HI> They re&s;olve to impeach the king, who is removed to Wind&s;or. &sect; <HI>LV.</HI> The ordinance for impeaching the king rejected by the upper house. &sect; <HI>LVI.</HI>
