to prince George of Denmark. &sect; <HI>LXII.</HI> The king is reconciled to Monmouth, who neverth$le&s;s is &s;oon di&s;graced. &sect; <HI>LXIII.</HI> Sketch of affairs on the continent. &sect; <HI>LXIV.</HI> The great credit and arbitrary di&s;po&s;ition of the duke of York. &sect; <HI>LXV.</HI> The king's death. &sect; <HI>LXVI.</HI> His character.</P>
